    &lt;Title&gt;2 week cancer pathway&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Christine Jones&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;In July I was referred by my GP on to the 2 week cancer pathway and am pleased to say it worked.  Within 2 weeks I had a variety of tests and procedures including an MRI scan all at Stepping Hill.  Every member of staff both admin and medical were wonderful and seemed aware of my anxiety and fear .  After each test I was notified of the results very quickly.  It is unfortunate that I am not allowed to mention by name individual staff members but would like to record special thanks and appreciation to the nurses on the Jasmine Suite who were so kind and reassuring to me and went that extra mile.  The pharmacist at the hospital also gave excellent service when collecting my medication . I was able to speak directly to the secretary of my Consultant who gave me a lot of her time and made enquiries on my behalf and always phoned me back.  Staff in Urology were also great but it was unfortunate that a male doctor had to do my procedure but I understand this was due to staff shortages and making sure I was seen promptly.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
